{
  "text": "Welcome to the ClipSpark pilot test episode. Today I want to share three things that changed everything about how I grow my podcast. The first thing I learned is that posting less content can actually grow your audience faster. I spent six months posting every single day and my numbers barely moved. Then I took a two week break, came back with one deeply researched episode per week, and my downloads tripled in ninety days. The second insight is about the first sixty seconds of your episode. Most podcasters spend their intro talking about themselves. Your listeners don't care who you are yet. Start with the most surprising thing you're going to say in the episode. Lead with the punchline. Trust me, the context can come later. Stop trying to go viral and start trying to be useful to a specific person. I have a listener named Sarah. She's a freelance designer trying to build a podcast about creative burnout. I make every episode for Sarah. Not for the algorithm. Not for the charts. For Sarah. And funnily enough, when I started doing that, my show started growing faster than when I was chasing downloads.",
